Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.00,0:00:35.85,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,The year is 1956. January 4th.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.85,0:00:42.93,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Early into the new year, Yamamoto Shinichi is traveling to Osaka on the Tsubame express train.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.50,0:00:47.91,Thought,,0,0,0,,Toda-sensei said, "What Kansai needs right now \Nis to be reminded of the basics of faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.41,0:00:53.85,Thought,,0,0,0,,If we don't stick closely to its sobering principle, \Nwe risk turning into a mindless mob."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.85,0:00:58.66,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'll start with a thorough lecture \Non Buddhism for all branch members.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.66,0:01:01.35,Thought,,0,0,0,,During January and February, \Nall Kansai executives
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.35,0:01:04.73,Thought,,0,0,0,,will be proactively providing \Nindividual religious guidance.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.73,0:01:11.84,Thought,,0,0,0,,We'll use that to strengthen the members' faith \Nand help them find joy in believing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.84,0:01:16.10,Thought,,0,0,0,,Then they'll channel that joy \Ninto their conversion efforts.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.10,0:01:20.54,Thought,,0,0,0,,That way, we can revitalize the organization \Nand make this energy self-sustainable.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.54,0:01:23.60,Thought,,0,0,0,,This trip to Osaka will decide everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.60,0:01:32.34,Thought,,0,0,0,,As one Western philosopher once said, \N"First, be bold; second, be bold; third, be bold." {dunno what he's talking about, only found "Be bold, be bold, and \Neverywhere be bold." by Herbert Spencer}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.34,0:01:34.62,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's not the time to be afraid!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.14,0:01:42.50,Thought,,0,0,0,,So this is our Kansai headquarters? It's huge!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.98,0:01:46.02,Thought,,0,0,0,,It might even be bigger \Nthan our Tokyo headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.02,0:01:50.97,Thought,,0,0,0,,Our Kansai comrades must be happy to have such a splendid base of operations built for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.03,0:01:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.32,0:01:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been expecting you!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.99,0:01:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Sei-chan! \NImpressive stronghold you got here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.81,0:02:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! It's our treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.16,0:02:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you'll have all the support in the world. {lit: you can fight to the fullest - meaning nothing would hold him back}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.32,0:02:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.49,0:02:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But to be honest, I was worried sick \Nabout what would happen to me here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.67,0:02:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.37,0:02:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.19,0:02:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, it's Sei-chan!\NCome on in. {/Sei-chan of Haruki's = of the Haruki family}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.71,0:02:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm telling you, it's a big deal for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.24,0:02:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They told me to run \Nfor the House of Councillors next year.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.68,0:02:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't have the confidence \Nto take on such a big role.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.14,0:02:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, I'm at a loss...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.79,0:02:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I was also just recently \Nput in charge of the Kansai region.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.58,0:02:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the first time for both of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.55,0:02:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it won't be easy, but you're fighting \Nto realize Sensei's vision, isn't that good enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.55,0:03:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more than enough, but it doesn't help \Nthe fact that I have no idea what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.39,0:03:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He—the unstoppable pitcher—became so timid when the time has come to win some election!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.42,0:03:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd rather be on the mound right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.46,0:03:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But alas, I suppose campaigning \Nis a far cry from pitching.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.32,0:03:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't make your dreams come true \Nif you're timid, Sei-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.76,0:03:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go in with full determination, we'll do our best, and leave the rest in Buddha's hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.73,0:03:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome, Seichiro-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.69,0:03:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry for barging in.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.63,0:03:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you parents doing all well?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.00,0:03:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. My mother and father spend their days \Nbuzzing around like busy bees.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.47,0:03:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Since it seems like we can't win either way,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.97,0:03:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,let's not lose sleep over it and just do \Nwhat we have to, as best we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.48,0:03:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Sei-chan, our battle is finally here. \NHang on tight now!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.40,0:03:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. The district executives \Nare waiting for you, Department Head.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.03,0:03:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.40,0:03:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.64,0:03:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.72,0:04:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm counting on your cooperation, friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.62,0:04:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.41,0:04:08.92,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,At that time the World-Honored One \Ncalmly arose from his samadhi... {check notes}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.92,0:04:11.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,Studying the Lotus Sutra \Nis also the military science. {it's technically a quite but w/e}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.65,0:04:17.72,Thought,,0,0,0,,Offering a prayer to the Lotus Sutra is a fundamental tactics for winning every battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.72,0:04:19.55,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,Nam Myoho Renge Kyo...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.55,0:04:22.70,Thought,,0,0,0,,This service feels so fresh \Nwith the Department Head around!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.70,0:04:25.06,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'll be coming to every service from now on!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.06,0:04:28.68,Thought,,0,0,0,,This service really cleanses the mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.68,0:04:33.96,Thought,,0,0,0,,Yes. Everyone is breathing in sync. \NWe can definitely do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.78,0:04:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take charge of this upcoming battle \Non behalf of President Toda!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.56,0:04:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Fight with confidence—\Nyour back is covered.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.65,0:04:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, our greatest hope and goal \Nis to win the upcoming July battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.74,0:05:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But let me be blunt with you, top executives:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.16,0:05:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,with our current influence in Kansai, \Nvictory is out of reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.18,0:05:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Our Osaka converts make up less than a third \Nof the households converted in Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.25,0:05:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone can tell you that, with these odds, \Nvictory is all but impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.57,0:05:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You're probably thinking the same yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.36,0:05:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But let's not forget that our branch \Nreceived a special Lotus Sutra scroll. {gohonzon}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.41,0:05:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The Wish for Prosperity Dharma
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.24,0:05:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,has the power to make possible what conventional wisdom would consider impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.77,0:05:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, this battle will begin \Nwith each and every Kansai member
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.30,0:05:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,demonstrating strong, prayerful devotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.44,0:05:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,When everyone chants in unison \Nto the Lotus Sutra,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.80,0:05:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the path to achieving the impossible \Nunfolds before our eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.41,0:05:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.93,0:05:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! \NIt's as he says!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.57,0:05:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.90,0:05:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Followers in every district must have unwavering trust in you, the district chief, and your staff. {地区員の方々は地区部長 地区担当員である皆さんを信頼しています}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.34,0:05:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Please extend your utmost solicitude to these people.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.96,0:06:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Meet with the followers in your district individually and listen to what they have to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.80,0:06:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure to convey to them that faith can resolve the worries and troubles they're facing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.02,0:06:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Speak with integrity and conviction.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.60,0:06:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.98,0:06:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Never give in to panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.21,0:06:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There is not the slightest need \Nto talk to anyone about the July battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.42,0:06:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I ask you now to extend a guiding hand
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.68,0:06:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to every single follower \Nin every corner of the Kansai region.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.20,0:06:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's essential to rekindle your own faith \Nin order to inspire faith in others.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.06,0:06:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you say, friends? \NCan you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.90,0:06:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we can!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.73,0:06:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you do it for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.30,0:06:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we'll do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.82,0:06:48.77,Thought,,0,0,0,,There's still a bit of time left.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.49,0:06:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, let's sing Kuroda Bushi together! {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kuroda_Bushi}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.23,0:06:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.79,0:06:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You know it, right? The famous folk song from Chikuzen Province, Kuroda Bushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.77,0:06:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's sing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.32,0:07:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.32,0:07:06.11,Thought,,0,0,0,,All right, guess I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.11,0:07:19.94,Song,,0,0,0,,Sake, you drink it, drink it!\NIf you drink it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.48,0:07:34.11,Song,,0,0,0,,Rising Sun's\NBest lance, this,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.95,0:07:49.44,Song,,0,0,0,,You will get it;\NIf you can drink it all,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.44,0:08:05.01,Song,,0,0,0,,You'd be the best of\NKuroda's bushi!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.85,0:08:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.10,0:08:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That felt great!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.89,0:08:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's time to charge into battle, \Nwe'll do it like this—singing and dancing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.28,0:08:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us advance with joy, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.82,0:08:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.78,0:08:30.01,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The 10 p.m. {\i1}Moonlight{\i0} overnight train
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.01,0:08:33.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,rocked Shinichi in its stiff seats \Non his way back to Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.31,0:08:36.58,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Travel between Tokyo and Osaka
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.58,0:08:41.96,Narrator,,0,0,0,,took 8 hours by express like the {\i1}Tsubame{\i0}, \Nand 11 by night train.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.96,0:08:44.96,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It would arrive at Tokyo Station \Ntomorrow at 9 a.m.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.96,0:08:49.11,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Constant trips between east and west \Nwere wearing down Shinichi,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.11,0:08:52.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,whose health was never strong to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.36,0:08:54.70,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'm tired...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.16,0:08:59.79,Thought,,0,0,0,,But at the very least, we managed \Nto complete the first phase of our plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.79,0:09:04.98,Thought,,0,0,0,,All that remains is to stick to the schedule \Nand tread carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.71,0:09:07.98,Thought,,0,0,0,,All right, let's write a postcard for everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.80,0:09:15.95,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Shinichi sent postcards of encouragement to Tatsuoka Gan and Mitsui Katsutoshi,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.95,0:09:20.04,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the Osaka Branch Coordinators, \Nas well Asada Katsumi and Oya Yoshihiko
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.04,0:09:22.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the local Youth Division members,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.65,0:09:25.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,whom he depended on to lead \NSoka Gakkai's future in Osaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.42,0:09:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how about another serving?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.38,0:09:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no, I'm full! This sukiyaki tasted great after all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.82,0:09:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Glad to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.49,0:09:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll make some tea now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.58,0:09:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.54,0:09:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish you luck with your work this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.40,0:09:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.92,0:09:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,As you probably know, I've been put in charge of the Osaka branch,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.20,0:09:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,so I likely won't be able \Nto run the company myself as much as I'd like to.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.18,0:09:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means I'll need to count on you all to step up and help run the business for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.77,0:10:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be fine! Don't worry \Nand put all your energy into campaigning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.50,0:10:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.94,0:10:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But chief...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.71,0:10:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard some executives say that you got the short end of the stick. You really don't mind that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.30,0:10:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Let them say whatever they want.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.57,0:10:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't know the outcome \Nof a battle until it's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.78,0:10:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do whatever it takes \Nto live up to Sensei's expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.23,0:10:25.95,Narrator,,0,0,0,,On January 14th, Shinichi boarded \Nthe 12:30 p.m. {\i1}Hato{\i0} express to Osaka,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.95,0:10:31.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,where he devoted himself to a study session for prospective Kansai Headquarters teaching staff,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.66,0:10:35.61,Narrator,,0,0,0,,whose appointment exams were scheduled for the next day.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.61,0:10:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Whew... People in Kansai \Nhave so much resolve. Impressive!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.62,0:10:44.95,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At 1:00 p.m. on the 15th, \Nthe first written portion of the appointment exam
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.95,0:10:48.31,Narrator,,0,0,0,,began in classrooms \Nat a nearby middle school.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.31,0:10:52.05,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The applicants came from all over the Kansai region,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.05,0:10:58.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,including some from as far away as Shikoku and Chugoku, totaling 423.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.78,0:11:01.14,Thought,,0,0,0,,Everyone takes this test very seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.14,0:11:03.11,Thought,,0,0,0,,Where else in the world would you find
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.11,0:11:06.08,Thought,,0,0,0,,ordinary people study the Buddhist philosophy so profoundly?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.62,0:11:13.07,Thought,,0,0,0,,It is fair to say that the spirit of seeking the truth has rooted itself firmly in the Kansai region.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.07,0:11:18.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The first round of interviews on this day and the second round on January 29th
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.24,0:11:20.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,resulted in 229 people passing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.66,0:11:30.17,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The number of Education Department staff \Nin Kansai more than doubled: from 150 to 379.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.65,0:11:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So first, I'd like to ask you about the battles you have been fighting over the past 10 days.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.34,0:11:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Tatsuoka-san, how was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.74,0:11:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I was surprised by how many of our members \Ncan't even perform a basic service.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.12,0:11:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't practice the basics of faith, \Nyou can't possibly manifest any merit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.71,0:11:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we should begin with daily home visits \Nto help members master the service.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.76,0:12:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What does the women's division have to say?\NHirosaka-san from Sakai Branch?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.81,0:12:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Since most of our followers are facing financial hardship or health issues,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.52,0:12:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the best we can do is listen with care \Nand offer encouragement.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.05,0:12:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized we need to elevate the role of chanting \Nand energize the members
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.53,0:12:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to ensure the success of individual guidance. {よほど題目を上げ生命力をつけておかなくては個人指導はできないことを 痛感しました}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.18,0:12:22.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Shinichi wanted to see how well his earlier policy—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.03,0:12:25.83,Narrator,,0,0,0,,"thorough individual guidance for members,"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.83,0:12:29.81,Narrator,,0,0,0,,proposed at the district chiefs' meeting—\Nwas being put into action.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.27,0:12:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.56,0:12:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen, let's redouble our efforts \Nin the individual guidance program.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.92,0:12:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, what's the situation \Non the Buddhist councils and officials
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.75,0:12:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,attending Sensei's lecture tomorrow? {ところで 明日の戸田先生の講義の結集状況や 役員の配置はどうなっていますか?}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.64,0:12:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I know Oya-kun is tasked with organizing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.42,0:12:53.96,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Shinichi meticulously prepared for the lectures on the Lotus Sutra and sacred scriptures,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.96,0:12:57.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,to be delivered by President Toda \Non the 16th and 17th.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.26,0:13:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, looks good to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.86,0:13:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, how many of our Kansai members \Nhave access to the scriptures?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.55,0:13:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,People who have \Nthe scriptures on their hands...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.41,0:13:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No one comes to mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.63,0:13:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, let's quickly have \Nthe teaching materials mimeographed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.34,0:13:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We must make sure everyone \Nfully understands Sensei's lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.41,0:13:32.43,Thought,,0,0,0,,This is the first time I've seen someone go to such lengths to properly welcome Toda-sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.60,0:13:39.22,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,The Nakanoshima Central Public Hall \Nwas packed to capacity with 6,000 people
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.22,0:13:41.83,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,gathered for Toda's lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.83,0:13:45.22,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Still, more than 1,000 people \Noverflowed into the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.60,0:13:51.04,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda's first beginner-level lecture in Kansai on the Lotus Sutra's {\i1}Expedient Means{\i0} chapter
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.04,0:13:54.23,Narrator,,0,0,0,,began on schedule at 6:30 p.m. {定刻の午後6時半 戸田の関西における第一回の一級講義として法華経「方便品」の講義が開始された}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.23,0:14:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I've come here to give this lecture because I wish to see Osaka free from sickness and poverty.  {literally says "rid osakan earth of ..." but we could obfuscate it somehow, e.g. "alleviate the suffering of ..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.55,0:14:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That is my only desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.58,0:14:09.39,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei is amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.39,0:14:12.79,Thought,,0,0,0,,In an instant, he won over \Nthe hearts and minds of our Kansai followers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.79,0:14:17.67,Thought,,0,0,0,,His lectures are sure to drive the wedge of faith \Neven deeper into their hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.67,0:14:20.34,Thought,,0,0,0,,With this, our takeoff in Kansai is assured!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.34,0:14:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,First, I'd like to explain the meaning of the {\i1}Expedient Means{\i0} Chapter,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.60,0:14:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,which you recite each morning and evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.99,0:14:35.14,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Toda's first ever lecture on the Expedient Means Chapter in Osaka took place at the Kyoya Inn
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.14,0:14:37.30,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,on February 1st, 1953.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.30,0:14:41.74,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,On that occasion, \Nthe Osaka branch flag was presented,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.74,0:14:44.14,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,though fewer than 100 members attended.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.14,0:14:48.96,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Three years later, 6,000 members packed the Central Public Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.96,0:14:52.50,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,while 1,000 more stood outside in the cold wind,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.50,0:14:58.22,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,straining to catch every word from the speakers and refusing to leave until the very end.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.22,0:15:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think, \Nladies and gentlemen?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.72,0:15:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it our duty to share the joy of attending
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.39,0:15:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei's inspiring lectures—\Nand the joy of faith—with others?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.26,0:15:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's come together and achieve the remarkable results we hoped to present to Sensei
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.57,0:15:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,when he returns next month.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.10,0:15:25.84,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,On January 20, the Supreme Council met at Soka Gakkai Headquarters
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.84,0:15:28.22,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,and approved Education Department Head
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.22,0:15:33.89,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Yamadaira Chuuhei as an additional candidate for the national House of Councillors election.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.87,0:15:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,As I've said before,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.29,0:15:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,we need every Soka Gakkai member \Nto stand united and rise to battle to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.74,0:15:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the true unity rooted in faith \Nis in fact hard to achieve.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.35,0:15:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, \Nlet's say we have a bottle of sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.60,0:15:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,One of you men would say "Bottoms up!"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.06,0:16:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and the next moment \Nyou are all united in that drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.03,0:16:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a sake bottle unity.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.44,0:16:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If this were a women's division meeting—\Nsay, with a decorated cake in front of us—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.38,0:16:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,one would say "Let's eat it!" and we'd instantly \Nbe united in the joy of eating it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.22,0:16:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But once the drinks are gone \Nand the cake's been eaten,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.73,0:16:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that sense of unity fades, \Nand we go back to minding our own business.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.04,0:16:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's easy to come together over drinks and sweets, \Nbut not so easy to unite for the battle ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.47,0:16:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We each have our own personalities, habits, \Nways of doing things, and ways of thinking—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.62,0:16:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,so how do we bring them into harmony?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.47,0:16:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you can think of all sorts \Nof worldly strategies for campaigning,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.50,0:16:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,but to me, they're just unimportant particulars.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.65,0:16:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not the driving force \Nthat will determine our ultimate victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.59,0:16:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Our unity comes from diverse individuals \Nsharing a single purpose. {lit: different bodies, single mind}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.58,0:17:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing we do will truly matter until we place the Lotus Sutra firmly at the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.92,0:17:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Only then the true unity of faith \Nis born for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.06,0:17:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not about the technicalities \Nof running an organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.28,0:17:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about devotion in everything we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.74,0:17:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, if we foster the understanding of faith through personal guidance,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.15,0:17:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,people will eagerly jump on board to help our cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.06,0:17:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And that takes time \Nand a great deal of patience.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.74,0:17:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Never forget—even in your sleep—that unlike unities built on alcohol, sweets, or money,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.66,0:17:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,no bond in this world is as strong, unwavering, and beautiful
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.24,0:17:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,as the one formed by our common faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.34,0:17:48.53,Thought,,0,0,0,,I came to Osaka at Sensei's request,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.53,0:17:52.29,Thought,,0,0,0,,not knowing our strategy for the Kansai Battle \Nhad been right all along. {大阪は先生の言われた通いにしてきた関西の戦いの方針は決して間違っていない!}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.49,0:17:57.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Many local leaders \Ntook Toda's guidance that day
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.03,0:18:01.68,Narrator,,0,0,0,,merely as an advice on strategy\Nin their personal struggles.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.68,0:18:04.13,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It is easy to follow your master's lead,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.13,0:18:08.06,Narrator,,0,0,0,,but it's hard to accept your master's \Nconvictions as your own. {師弟の道を歩むのは易しく師弟不二の道を貫く困難さがここにある}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.06,0:18:11.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto Shinichi was different, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.94,0:18:16.89,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The basis of Shinichi's strategy \Nwas exactly the same as that outlined by Toda—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.89,0:18:18.79,Narrator,,0,0,0,,they were totally on the same page.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.83,0:18:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,...Such is the situation in Osaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.25,0:18:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Start by preparing for a battle \Nthat far exceeds any expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.21,0:18:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomii-kun, Ueda-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.79,0:18:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.76,0:18:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I know this six-month assignment \Nwon't be easy on you,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.30,0:18:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,but I need you to become my hands and feet \Nand move freely within Osaka. {これから約半年 長期の派遣で ご苦労だが 今回は私の手足となって縦横無尽に大阪で働いてもらいたい}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.19,0:18:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And your reward will be the glorious memory \Nof a once-in-a-lifetime struggle—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.04,0:18:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,fighting to make the impossible possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.38,0:18:56.39,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Both Tomii Rinsaku and Ueda Tojiro \Nwere up-and-coming district chiefs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.39,0:19:00.56,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The two were selected as leaders of the team
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.56,0:19:05.14,Narrator,,0,0,0,,sent from Tokyo to assist \Nin the upcoming Battle for Osaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.14,0:19:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe Osaka Prefecture can be divided into five districts, as I've done here with the red lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.83,0:19:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.78,0:19:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Osaka City can be divided \Ninto two blocks for north and south.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.86,0:19:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And the remaining three blocks
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.89,0:19:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,follow the old division of the provinces of Settsu, Kawachi, and Izumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.52,0:19:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This division is well thought-through. \NLet's go with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.27,0:19:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,As for the assignments...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.03,0:19:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, Tomii-kun, let's put you \Nin charge of the first precinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.78,0:19:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. I got you covered.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.62,0:19:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Ueda-kun, can you take on \Nthe second precinct?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.84,0:19:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I'll be glad to.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.28,0:19:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I doubt we'd find a better match
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.83,0:19:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to partner with you among our Osaka executives \Nthan Mitsui Katsutoshi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.79,0:19:52.25,Thought,,0,0,0,,Huh? That overly cautious guy \Nwho's twenty years my senior?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.68,0:19:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,For Ueda-kun, the energetic \NTatsuoka Gan-kun would be a good match.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.05,0:20:00.38,Thought,,0,0,0,,Huh? That fireplug with assertiveness of a tank? {lit: vigorous person who is like a tankette = meaning he's short but sturdily built and energetic}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.38,0:20:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomii-kun, you're smart and ballsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.22,0:20:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you get carried away, there's a risk \Nyour youth will lead you down a reckless path.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.86,0:20:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you pair up with the seasoned and cool-headed Mitsui-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.32,0:20:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the two of you will form \Na stable and active duo. {/stable and active}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.09,0:20:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ueda-kun, you are mild-mannered, \Nbut that slow pace is your weakness.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.82,0:20:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we balance it \Nwith Tatsuoka's aggressiveness,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.85,0:20:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll offset each other's weaknesses \Nand make your campaigning steady and effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.83,0:20:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, we want to create a perfect combination of conservative and innovative.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.36,0:20:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just a whim.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.72,0:20:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I have come this far after undergoing rigorous training under Toda-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.26,0:20:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He taught me everything he knows about managing human resources.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.47,0:20:49.48,Thought,,0,0,0,,Chief really thought everything through \Nbefore deciding on a course of action...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.48,0:20:55.44,Thought,,0,0,0,,All right! Now that this is settled, \NI'm ready to fight to the death in Osaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.26,0:21:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, Sei-chan,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.46,0:21:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,are personal guidance interviews \Nand home visits progressing as planned?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.37,0:21:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, good to know.\NKeep up the good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.40,0:21:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be there two days before the joint meeting \Nof the two branches on the 19th.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.11,0:21:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Till then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.49,0:21:24.73,Thought,,0,0,0,,We can use this joint meeting as a springboard to let the wave of individual guidance
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.73,0:21:29.10,Thought,,0,0,0,,now emerging across Japan \Nsweep through all of Kansai.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.10,0:21:33.92,Thought,,0,0,0,,Eventually, this driving force will form \Nthe impenetrable fortress of Common Path...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.92,0:21:39.11,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's it! I should turn these feelings into a song \Nand dedicate it to Sensei on his birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.84,0:21:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, congratulations on your birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.07,0:21:44.79,Top,,0,0,0,,Though it's nothing grand,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.79,0:21:48.47,Top,,0,0,0,,please accept this token of good wishes \Nfrom the Daito Trading employees.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.47,0:21:49.89,Top,,0,0,0,,Oh, thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.89,0:21:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And also this—an embodiment \Nof my current feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.56,0:21:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Please accept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.37,0:22:12.33,Thought,,0,0,0,,Is he referring to the legendary
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.33,0:22:16.88,Thought,,0,0,0,,Jinzhou City Fortress in Liaoning Province, China, \Nfamed in history as impregnable?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.52,0:22:21.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,Yes, Shinichi is definitely capable of building it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.32,0:22:27.64,Thought,,0,0,0,,What a joy it is to gaze upon Jinzhou Castle, \Nbuilt by Shinichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.95,0:22:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.58,0:22:52.65,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,The kickoff rallies \Nfor the Osaka and Sakai branches
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.65,0:22:57.61,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,were held on February 19th \Nat the Central Public Hall in Nakanoshima.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.17,0:23:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,With such a magnificent battle formation,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.36,0:23:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,let us extend the grace \Nof the Lotus Sutra to all of Kansai
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.09,0:23:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and fulfill President Toda's design!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.97,0:23:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That is our declaration! {右宣言}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.50,0:23:19.08,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Following Branch Chief Mitsui's \Ndeclaration of struggle,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.08,0:23:22.26,Narrator,,0,0,0,,it was Yamamoto Shinichi's turn to speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.18,0:23:32.83,Top,,0,0,0,,The upcoming Battle for Kansai \Nwill be a full-scale religious revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.83,0:23:37.44,Top,,0,0,0,,When we hear the word "revolution," we often picture violent uprisings and bloodshed—
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.44,0:23:41.84,Top,,0,0,0,,but the revolution brought about through Nichiren Daishonin's Buddhism
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.84,0:23:45.20,Top,,0,0,0,,is one that'll save humanity \Nwithout spilling a single drop of blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.20,0:23:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This religious revolution begins with a personal human revolution within each of us—
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.01,0:23:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,a transformation of our own lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.25,0:23:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Our missionary work \Nisn't for the benefit of Soka Gakkai,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.25,0:24:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,nor is it for the sake \Nof the Osaka and Sakai branches.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.21,0:24:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Not long ago, our lives were steeped in misery and despair, trapped by a misguided faith—
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.24,0:24:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,but now, through the power of Lotus Sutra, \Nwe're rising to transform our destiny,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.31,0:24:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,awaken happiness from within, \Nand shine that light into the lives of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.81,0:24:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.61,0:24:23.42,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.42,0:24:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.49,0:24:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us intensify our individual guidance efforts \Nthroughout February and March
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.66,0:24:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to bring happiness \Nto as many followers as possible—
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.78,0:24:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and beyond that, let us boldly expand our propagation and educational work
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.42,0:24:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,with the passionate spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.96,0:24:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of revealing the profound greatness \Nof this Dharma to the people of Osaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.09,0:24:58.12,Top,,0,0,0,,Just as Tokyo is the political and cultural center, \NOsaka is the economic center of Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.12,0:25:03.52,Top,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it's safe to say that Osaka residents should be more business-savvy than Tokyoites.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.52,0:25:06.46,Top,,0,0,0,,They would never do \Nanything wasteful or unprofitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.46,0:25:12.33,Top,,0,0,0,,It's clear that people in Osaka are hardworking \Nand always open for business. {lit: keep doing things that bring profits or profitable - trying to give it a positive spin without calling them greedy}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.89,0:25:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This holds true for both business and faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.18,0:25:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about it: the five morning services \Ntake at least 30 minutes,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.76,0:25:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,plus 20 more minutes \Nfor the three evening services.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.37,0:25:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll also need candles, incense, \Nand potted star anise. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Illicium_anisatum}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.75,0:25:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you also have to attend roundtable discussions and find time to preach.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.96,0:25:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,All this for no personal gain or profit whatsoever. {これだけのことをもしあなた方が 何の得をすることももうかることもなかったら}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.43,0:25:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think? \NIsn't it a waste of everyone's time?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.46,0:25:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,People often say, "faith that doesn't reward \Nits followers is useless," and I agree. {divine grace; divine favour; blessing; answer to a prayer​}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.91,0:25:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.92,0:25:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,By believing in this Dharma and chanting before the altar,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.37,0:26:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we draw closer to the Buddha—\Nwe step into his shoes. {lit: we become the same as buddha, we make our life's circumstances/position/state of being like that of buddha}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.33,0:26:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No Buddha has ever lived in poverty—
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.23,0:26:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've never heard of one \Nwasting away in bed with tuberculosis.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.34,0:26:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.13,0:26:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No one's ever seen a Buddha \Nchased down by debt collectors!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.05,0:26:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.55,0:26:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.52,0:26:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You embraced this faith to find happiness—
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.86,0:26:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,so chant before the altar as you should, \Nand let the Buddha's grace flow into your life. {/receive plenty of merit}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.40,0:26:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,30 minutes in the morning and \N20 in the evening is enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.78,0:26:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Candles and incense \Nare all the inventory you'll need.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.72,0:26:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're asked \Nto take on a conversion task,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.22,0:26:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,don't just say “I'll do my best” \Nsimply out of sense of duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.63,0:26:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you're truly blessed, \Nyou'll be eager to convert others yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.63,0:26:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,then your energy for the conversion work \Nbecomes nearly infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.59,0:26:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.42,0:26:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I will continue to come to Osaka \Ntwice a month to give lectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.59,0:26:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason I'm doing this
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.72,0:27:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,is because I want everyone to be free of illness \Nand break free from poverty as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.62,0:27:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.54,0:27:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold fast to your faith and be well—so that you thrive in business and become well-to-do!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.38,0:27:20.83,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The Osaka branch went into overdrive. {/All of Osaka members were fired up.}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.83,0:27:23.71,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It wasn't just the members sent from Tokyo—
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.71,0:27:28.17,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Osaka's entire leadership united \Nin stepping up their home visit efforts.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.06,0:27:31.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,With individual guidance \Nmore intense than ever,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.57,0:27:34.15,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the phrase \N"Candles and incense are all you need"
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.15,0:27:39.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,became the campaign's motto, spreading through Osaka like wildfire.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.10,0:27:42.58,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The launch of the home guidance program everywhere at once
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.58,0:27:45.41,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was quickly reflected \Nin the roundtable discussions.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.41,0:27:50.74,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The number of participants surged, \Nand new faces began joining every roundtable,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.74,0:27:53.78,Narrator,,0,0,0,,injecting fresh energy into the discussions.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.57,0:27:58.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Many members had only recently joined \Nand their faith was still growing,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.57,0:28:04.17,Narrator,,0,0,0,,but the roundtable discussions let them hear the guidance of seniors and the experiences of peers,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.17,0:28:09.55,Narrator,,0,0,0,,helping them understand the great merits of the Lotus Dharma and strengthen their devotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.86,0:28:14.61,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The members who emerged \Nfrom these roundtable discussions
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.61,0:28:21.14,Narrator,,0,0,0,,eagerly stood up and took on the conversion and educational work of their own accord.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.92,0:28:27.92,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Although the Kansai Branch had focused \Non intensifying individual guidance this month,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.92,0:28:33.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the conversion results in February—\N3,986 households in the Osaka Branch
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.65,0:28:40.44,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and 697 in the Sakai Branch—\Nfar exceeded January's numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.44,0:28:45.96,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It's safe to say that Yamamoto Shinichi's determination to make the impossible possible
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.96,0:28:50.92,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was now resonating in the hearts \Nof all the members in Kansai.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.62,0:29:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a magnificent castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.18,0:29:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Shin-chan, the Jinzhou Castle \Nyou're already building in your imagination
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.23,0:29:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is probably just as magnificent, \Nbeautiful, and sturdy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.07,0:29:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.50,0:29:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.86,0:29:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The castle of victory for the Common Path.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.45,0:29:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The castle of diverse individuals sharing a single purpose. {different bodies one mind again}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.57,0:29:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,A people's castle of happiness and peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.44,0:29:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where you'll build it, \Nyour Jinzhou Castle...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.72,0:29:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Still invisible to others, \Nbut visible to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.85,0:29:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It shines in golden colors,\Nthe Castle of Common Path. {and Lotus Sutra}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.91,0:29:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no castle in the world \Nmore exalted than this! {/noble/divine}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.92,0:29:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't wait to see that castle materialize, while I'm still in good health...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.90,0:30:01.33,Thought,,0,0,0,,Now we absolutely \Nhave to win the Battle of Osaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.33,0:30:06.00,Thought,,0,0,0,,The impregnable Jinzhou Castle \Ncan only emerge from a victorious battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.20,0:30:14.96,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei, just watch it unfold. \NWe will definitely win this!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.96,0:30:19.59,Thought,,0,0,0,,The castle of the people's victory—\Nthe Jinzhou Castle—we'll build it no matter what!
Comment: 0,0:30:19.59,0:30:21.59,Thought,,0,0,0,,
